Title: About KABi
Text:
KABi Technologies is a global HR technology company founded in 2018, specializing in
AI-powered talent solutions aimed at revolutionizing the human capital industry. Headquartered
in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, with additional offices in Dubai, UAE, and other locations across the
Middle East, USA, and UK, KABi combines deep market knowledge and innovative AI-driven
approaches to transform human capital practices. The company's mission is to empower
businesses to exceed their potential through digital transformation while upholding core values
such as prioritizing human capital, fostering growth, building a strong community of "KABians,"
and driving innovation. KABi offers a range of products, including HYRDD, INVIEWS, and HC
Consulting, to support businesses in achieving their HR objectives. For inquiries, contact
hello@kabi.ai.
Leadership and Expertise Driving KABi's Success
and Growth
KABi Technologies is guided by a distinguished board with extensive local and international
expertise, committed to fostering business growth, sustainability, and strategic governance. Led
by Chairman Abdulrahman Alaiban, the board emphasizes effective oversight and the adoption
of strong corporate governance frameworks to drive success.
The management team at KABi brings over 100 years of collective experience in HR and
technology, providing exceptional leadership to create a positive work environment and ensure
company success. Key leaders include CEO Khalid Aloraij, Deputy CEO Dr. Ahmad Khamis,
and other executives, such as the Chief Operating Officer, Chief Information Officer, and Heads
of various departments, all contributing to KABi's continuous growth and innovation.

Title: KABi Culture
Text:
KABi Technologies fosters a corporate culture that prioritizes collaboration, inclusivity, and
results. They value cultural diversity, believing it drives innovation, creativity, and improves
communication. Their workplace culture is designed to boost employee engagement, enhance
brand reputation, and promote adaptability.

Title: Statistics and Insights
Text:
KABi Technologies is a leading provider of AI-powered solutions focused on transforming the
HR landscape. With a client-centric approach, KABi leverages advanced AI to streamline HR
processes, improve candidate experiences, and drive business agility. They bring proven
product quality, extensive expertise in HR and technology, and a global, diversified client base.
Key statistics highlight the need for digital transformation in HR:
88% of companies use AI in HR.
76% of hiring managers struggle with attracting the right candidates.
52% of recruitment leaders find screening large candidate pools challenging.
84% of recruiters prioritize cultural fit in hiring.
60% of candidates abandon job applications due to length and complexity.
69% of companies have repeatable processes, yet only 4% manage them effectively.
78% of companies have engagement strategies, but only 43% implement them successfully.
KABi helps businesses address these challenges by offering innovative solutions that improve
HR efficiency, enhance data analysis, and foster higher employee engagement, ensuring
companies stay competitive in a rapidly evolving digital landscape.
KABi APIs and Services

Title: File2text
Text:
The File2Text API, is a tool that converts files like PDFs and Word documents into text. It takes
a file as input, along with a unique ID to track the request, and provides the extracted text, the
type of file, and the languages detected in the content. For example, it can identify if the file is in
English or Arabic. This API is easy to use and helps simplify file processing by turning
documents into readable text for further use.

Title: Job parser
Text:
The Job Parser API analyzes job descriptions and extracts structured details about the role. It
takes inputs like a job description and a unique request ID, returning information such as job
title, experience level, sectors, company details, location, required skills, salary range, and
qualifications. For instance, it parses a description for a "Senior Artificial Intelligence Engineer,"
identifying required skills like Python, TensorFlow, and Machine Learning, experience in
construction, and a salary range of $2000-$3000 per month. This API simplifies job data
processing, making it ideal for HR systems and recruitment platforms.

Title: Salary index
Text:
The AI-Powered Salary Prediction feature uses advanced AI and a comprehensive salary
database to estimate fair compensation for job seekers and employers. It considers factors like
skills, education, experience, job title, and location to provide detailed salary ranges. This tool
helps job seekers understand their market value and identify skills that can boost their earnings.
Employers can use it to set competitive salary ranges based on current market trends. By
cleaning and mapping job titles and using AI to predict similar roles when needed, it ensures
accurate and relevant salary insights for various positions and industries.
